snippet.textDisplay: Dave Filoni is the unsung hero of this Disney era. Despite working in the shadow of it's corporate stupidity and political agendas he puts the fans first and knows exactly what they want through his own love for Star Wars, instead of working to meet deadlines with rushed, incoherent plots that we ended up getting with the new films. Nothing but respect for the guy!

The franchise is not beyond saving. The sequel trilogy may have been a misfire, but Filoni will be one of many saviors. Hope, my friends, is not lost.
Btw, Maul foreshadowing Order 66 is dope. Why does he have a double-bladed lightsaber though? He only gets his Inquisitor-like weapon we see in Solo and Rebels after the Great Purge.
